---
description: Global project conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

# General

- Write concise, production-grade code.
- Prefer small, focused changes.
- Do not rewrite unrelated files.
- Preserve existing naming unless asked otherwise.

# Python

- Use Python type hints everywhere.
- Prefer explicit imports.
- Add docstrings only when they add real value.
- Avoid over-engineering.

# Output

- When proposing code changes, follow the existing project structure.
- Explain tradeoffs briefly when architecture is impacted.
